  "known_limitations": [
    "Import syntax limitation: 'import panther.math' fails because 'panther' is a keyword (TokenKind.PANTHER). Workaround: Package functions are globally available via self-hosted injection; import not required for function access.",
    "No cyclic dependency detection: Not yet implemented — packages currently have no dependency declarations.",
    "No duplicate-symbol detection across packages: If two packages define the same function name, the last one loaded wins.",
    "No public/private export control: All functions in __init__.pan are exported.",
    "No module object with dot access: Since 'panther' is a keyword, 'panther.math.abs()' not supported. Functions are flat names like 'panther_math_abs()'.",
    "Process package functions are stubs: 'panther_process_run', 'panther_process_spawn', etc. return error objects (not implemented).",
    "No object property iteration for 'in' operator: The 'key in obj' syntax doesn't work for objects (only arrays). Use 'obj[key] != null' pattern instead.",
    "Array slicing 'arr[start:end]' not supported: Use index-based access instead."
  ],
